        <div class=""aboutCard"">
            <p class=""text-center"">
                In most deckbuilding games, players would discard their entire hand at the end of their turn. In Imperium, they can keep the cards they don't use. This allows players to hold onto certain important cards for a later turn resulting in more strategic play.

                Unlike most deckbuilding games, Imperium imposes a resource cost for playing cards from the hand. Both players are assigned a hero at the start of the game giving them 5 resources to manage - health, mana, experience, abilities and gold. In most deckbuilding games, gold is the only manageable resource.

